<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=15220&amp;p=184282#p184282"><![CDATA[
It's a convention for some websites to open external links in a new tab, and internal links in the same tab.<br /><br />I don't personally find it necessary (if I want a new tab, I ask the browser for it), but if you're someone who relies on this convention it becomes irritating when it isn't there.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5165">rainwarrior</a> — Thu Dec 08, 2016 7:41 pm</p><hr />
